Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @Roma tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Halve @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Core, deseed, and cut @poblano pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Drain @black beans{13.4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving liquid.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, scallions, a big squeeze of lime juice, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and poblano; cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} and half the beans (you'll use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring, until fragrant and warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from heat.

Add half the @ground plant-based protein{9%oz} to pan with onion and poblano; cook, stirring occasionally until veggies are softened and plant-based protein is browned and warmed through, ~{5-6%minutes}. Cook through the rest of the step as instructed.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining beans and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add ¼ cup reserved bean liquid. Simmer until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Remove pot from heat; mash beans until mostly smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

Spread @flour tortillas{6} with mashed beans. Place a small amount of filling on one half of each tortilla, then sprinkle with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}(diced).

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create flautas. Place seam sides down on a #plate{}.

Wash out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add flautas seam sides down. Cook, carefully turning so they stay intact, until golden brown and crispy, ~{2%minutes} per side.

> Work in batches if necessary and watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide flautas between plates and top with @guacamole{4%tbsp}, pico de gallo, and @sour cream{4%tbsp}. (Alternatively, serve with toppings on the side for dipping.) Cut remaining lime half into wedges and serve on the side.